article.headline: Lafayette 76, Stony Brook 68
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. (AP) -- Andrew Brown tied the game near the end of regulation then had eight of his 21 points in overtime as Lafayette beat Stony Brook 76-68 on Monday night. Mitchell Beauford made two free throws with 29 seconds left in regulation to give Stony Brook a 59-57 lead, but Brown hit a jumper with 17 seconds left to send the game into overtime. The Leopards (1-1) scored the first eight points of the overtime, but Stony Brook got within 67-65 on two free throws by Michael Tyree. Brown then made five free throws as Lafayette closed the game with a 9-3 run. Bilal Abdullah had 15 points for Leopards, while Matt Betley and Michael Gruner both added 10. Ricky Lucas topped the Seawolves (0-2) with 18 points and Beauford had 13. Emanuel Neto had eight points and 13 rebounds for Stony Brook.
